{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638992","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638992"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:01:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:01:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17751"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17751"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.97,0,0,0,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10465"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74976"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10465","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10465"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17751"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60482"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1223"},{"type":"tags","id":"1353"},{"type":"tags","id":"1627"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7037"},{"type":"tags","id":"10948"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24429"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24431"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74976","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74976"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-year history of infertility despite regular unprotected intercourse. She reports irregular menstrual cycles and has noticed an increase in facial hair and acne over the past year. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is evidence of hirsutism on her face and acne on her back. An ultrasound reveals enlarged ovaries with multiple small follicles. Cushing\u0027s syndrome has been ruled out.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Polycystic ovary syndrome","Hypothyroidism","Hyperprolactinaemia","Premature ovarian insufficiency","Androgen-secreting tumour"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of \u003Cstrong\u003Epolycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)\u003C/strong\u003E, including infertility, irregular menstrual cycles, hirsutism, and acne. The ultrasound findings of enlarged ovaries with multiple small follicles further support this diagnosis. PCOS is a common endocrine disorder in women of reproductive age and is a leading cause of infertility due to anovulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can cause menstrual irregularities and infertility, but it is less likely to cause hirsutism and acne. Additionally, the ultrasound findings are more suggestive of PCOS.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHyperprolactinaemia\u003C/strong\u003E can also lead to menstrual irregularities and infertility, but it presents with galactorrhoea. The ultrasound findings are not characteristic of hyperprolactinaemia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPremature ovarian insufficiency\u003C/strong\u003E would present with symptoms of oestrogen deficiency, such as hot flushes and vaginal dryness, rather than hyperandrogenism. The ultrasound findings would show small or absent follicles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eandrogen-secreting tumour\u003C/strong\u003E could cause hirsutism and acne, but it would usually present with more rapid onset and severe symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is characterised by irregular menstrual cycles, hyperandrogenism, and polycystic ovaries on ultrasound.","PCOS is a common cause of infertility in women of reproductive age.","Hirsutism and acne are common clinical manifestations of hyperandrogenism in PCOS."],"references":["Dason ES, Koshkina O, Chan C, Sobel M. Diagnosis and management of polycystic ovarian syndrome. CMAJ. 2024 Jan 28;196(3):E85-E94. doi: 10.1503/cmaj.231251. Erratum in: CMAJ. 2024 Mar 3;196(8):E269. doi: 10.1503/cmaj.240216. Erratum in: CMAJ. 2024 Mar 17;196(10):E351. doi: 10.1503/cmaj.240303. PMID: 38286488; PMCID: PMC10833093.","Legro RS, Arslanian SA, Ehrmann DA, Hoeger KM, Murad MH, Pasquali R, Welt CK; Endocrine Society. Diagnosis and treatment of polycystic ovary syndrome: an Endocrine Society clinical practice guideline. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2013 Dec;98(12):4565-92. doi: 10.1210/jc.2013-2350. Epub 2013 Oct 22. Erratum in: J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2021 May 13;106(6):e2462. doi: 10.1210/clinem/dgab248. PMID: 24151290; PMCID: PMC5399492.","Christ JP, Cedars MI. Current Guidelines for Diagnosing PCOS. Diagnostics (Basel). 2023 Mar 15;13(6):1113. doi: 10.3390/diagnostics13061113. PMID: 36980421; PMCID: PMC10047373.","Trivax B, Azziz R. Diagnosis of polycystic ovary syndrome. Clin Obstet Gynecol. 2007 Mar;50(1):168-77. doi: 10.1097/GRF.0b013e31802f351b. PMID: 17304034."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60482"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17751"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60482","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60482"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T13:07:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T13:07:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10465"}},"conten